headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; The New Tabernacle Church--Laying the Corner-stone. The Expenses of the City Inspector's Department. Police Intelligence. Coroner's Inquests. AN EFFORT TO CAPTURE TAMMANY.

docs.lead_paragraph: The corner-stone of the new Church, in course of erection for the worshippers at the late Broadway Tabernacle, at the corner of Thirty-Fourth-street and Sixth-avenue, was laid yesterday in the presence of some hundreds of spectators, many of whom were ladies.

headline.main: KEY WEST.; Character of the Country--Occupations of the People--Miscellaneous.

docs.lead_paragraph: You say in your last letter, "How blue is actually known at the North about Key West, its business, inhabitants and more especially, of its climate." docs.lead_paragraph: The last day's session of Congress, previous to the holiday vacation, was marked by interesting proceedings in both Houses. The Kansas debate was continued in the Senate--Mr. STUART, Democratic member from Michigan, and Mr. BRODERICK, Democratic member from California, making speeches in opposition to the view of the President.

headline.main: NEW - ENGLAND SOCIETY OF NEW-YORK.; FIFTY-SECOND ANNIVERSARY BANQUET.

docs.lead_paragraph: Yesterday was Forefathers' day, 237th anniversary of the Pilgrims' landing at Plymouth. The New-England Society held its annual meeting at noon in the Astor, House. WM. CHAUNGY, Esq., was elected moderator. The Treasurer reported a balance on hand of $2,144. WM.
